commentTextItems.html: Match is over! Series is decided. Thanks for coming everyone. It's full and on the middle stump, Sammy, left alone with Richard Parker on a boat, has no option but to take a plunge. He goes for a big swing and misses. Middle stump takes a beating..

commentPostTextItems.html: They gave hope of a comeback, but it wasn't to be today. Thanks for all the comments and feedback, apologies as we get to publish only a handful. Dan Brettig's match-report is being updated as I type. This is Devashish Fuloria signing off, ciao ciao.
Shane Watson is the player of the match: "It was nice to be out there. It was a nice easy wicket. Once I got going -- I have been dreaming of this for the last four weeks. "

Australia have finished the job with precision. They put up a strong score, thanks to Shane Watson and Phil Hughes with the bat, and then their bowlers kept chipping away with the wickets. James Faulkner picked up four wickets - all four bowled. The pitch at Manuka Oval was supposed to give the West Indies team a respite after Perth, but they gave a few too many earlier. The Bravos kept them in the game for a while, but once they were out, there was no one really to stand up and be a hero today.
Dave: "WI have been given two very chaseable scores by Australia, and, after being in good position, lost both. Got to hurt your confidence."
Ashok: "This West Indies team batting line up is one of the most capable one but unfortunately they are yet to prove it."

dismissalComment.html: caught at deep square leg! Excellente catch!! Wow! Pollard flies in from nowhere and plucks a sure shot six with one hand. caught at deep midwicket! And another catch by Pollard. Another well-timed leap at the boundary. Bailey charged out of the crease and Narine pulled his length back, but the batsman goes for the pull anyway and gets a lot of bat on it. But no one is surprised as Polly pulls off another stunner

dismissalComment.html: that's the way to do it! He bowls it with some venom from wide off the crease, RH plays down the wrong line and the middle stump is knocked back. That was a screamer and Dwayne was left holding his defensive pose for a while.. Supaah

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle b Faulkner 2 (5b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: all over sir, it's all over JF goes ballistic. He has the big wicket. It was a length ball angling in to the batsman, Gayle tried to flick it to the leg side without moving his feet, the ball sneaks through the gap between the bat and pad and crashes on to the off and middle stump..

dismissalComment.html: oh my! from nowhere again. It was a quick short one on the body, the batsman drops it on the off side and calls for a quick single. dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy b Faulkner 8 (7b 0x4 1x6 18m) SR: 114.28

dismissalComment.html: Match is over! Series is decided. Thanks for coming everyone. It's full and on the middle stump, Sammy, left alone with Richard Parker on a boat, has no option but to take a plunge. He goes for a big swing and misses. Middle stump takes a beating..
